Mathesin enucleatam p. 38.)

Modus hic est: Fiat triang: &ae;quil: ABD, divis&ahat;&que; diametro AB in tot partes &ae;quales,&line;
quot laterum est figura inscribenda, duabus&que; earum &prae;termissis et &agrav; B vers&ugrav;s A, duca&tur;,&line;
per initium terti&ae; recta DF, & hinc recta FB, quam putat esse latus polygoni optati&line;
Anal: Sit secta diameter utcun&que; in E, e , duct&ae;&que;DEF, FA, & FB & demissa in diametrum per‐
pendicularis FG, fiat CB=a, CE vel Ce=b, FB=x, unde AF=\sqrt{\mathstrut}\,\overline{4aa-xx}&line;


    \begin{array}{ccccccc}
    AB & . & BF & :: & BF & . & BG. \\
    2a & . & x & :: & x & . & \dfrac{\mathstrut xx}{2a}
    \end{array}

